   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Israel Entering into the Good Land</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In Joshua 3 and 4 Israel entered into the good land.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>That was something of God's economy.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Israel Setting Up the Tabernacle</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>of the Ark in Shiloh</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Another aspect of the divine economy was Israel's setting up the tabernacle of the ark in Shiloh Josh 18:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>B. The Satanic Chaos with the Priests</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Again the satanic chaos followed the divine economy.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The Priests among Israel Being Degraded</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The priests among Israel became degraded and corrupt 1 Sam 2:12-17, 22-34 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The Ark Being Captured by Israel's Enemy</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In this chaotic situation, the ark, which was used in a superstitious way, was captured by Israel's enemy 1 Sam 4:1 5:2 .</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The priests were killed, and the ark was captured.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>C. The Divine Economy</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>with David, Solomon, and the Positive Prophets 1.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>God Raising Up David</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>as a Man after His Own Heart to Do His Will</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>In the divine economy, God raised up David as a man after His own heart to do His will 1 Sam 13:14 .</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>David Bringing Back the Ark of God</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>David brought back the ark of God 2 Sam 6:1-19 .</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>David Desiring to Build the Temple for God</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>and Preparing the Material</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>and the Site for the Building of God's Temple</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>David desired to build the temple for God and he prepared the material and the site for the building of God's temple 2 Sam 7:2; 1 Chron 22:1-19; 29:1-19; 2 Chron 3:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Solomon Building the Temple for God</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>and Bringing the Ark into the Temple</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Solomon built the temple for God and brought the ark into the temple 1 Kings 5:4-5; 6:2; 7:51 8:11 .</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>The Positive Prophets Ministering Faithfully</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>The positive prophets ministered faithfully, especially concerning Christ in the divine economy.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>They prophesied a great deal concerning Christ in the divine economy.</S>
   </TEXT>
